# Inline expansion rule (IDE display)

Use mapped-type expansion (`{ [K in keyof T]: T[K] }`) **only** when needed for public API ergonomics,
so IDE tooltips show concrete shapes instead of helper aliases.

- Allowed: exported/public result types (`SqlCreateTable`, `SqlSchema`, `SqlDatabase`, migration API result types).
- Avoid for internal reducers/helpers where a named helper keeps logic readable.
- Whenever this inline expansion is used, add a short comment explaining it is for IDE/API shape display.
